.....1....+....2....+....3....+....4....+....5....+....6....+....7....+....8
     F** This is the canonical "hello world" for the RPG II compiler.
     F** In Phase 1 it is parsed only for the F-spec record; nothing executes
     F** yet. It will gain meaning incrementally across Phases 2-5.
     F*
     F** Columns:            6 F = File spec line
     F**                  7-15  Filename
     F**                   19   File format (F=fixed)
     F**                   40   Device (DISK/PRINTER/WORKSTN)
     FEXAMPLR  IP  F  80     DISK
     C*
     C           EXAMPLR   SETON                      LR
